author: The Irish Times
title: Coronavirus: It will take 10 days to reach testing goal, says Harris
description: Minister for Health says global supplies shortage affecting Ireland
content:
It will probably take 10 days to fully ramp up lab services for coronavirus testing around the country, Minister for Health Simon Harris has said.
Testing will not change medical advice and anyone with symptoms must stay at home, he told RTÉ radio.
